    <h2 class='chart-headline'>Poverty-stricken Districts Have Led the Charge</h2>
    <p class='chart-description'>New York as a whole is recycling more, up from a diversion rate of 17% in 2009 to 19% in 2018. The jump is largely thanks to high-poverty community districts, where targeted community outreach played a role in boosting diversion rates.</p>
